Like, I could have realized that it was a rough patch but it wouldn't last forever.

message: Hey, I know things feel super tough right now, but trust me, it won't always be like this. Like, your brain can actually change over time, and that includes how you feel about stuff. So just because you feel this way now doesn't mean it's permanent. It might take a while, but things can get better, even if it's just little by little.
reflection: I felt super stuck when I didn't make the basketball team. At first, I was so bummed and thought I'd never be good enough. But thinking about it, maybe it doesn't have to be a permanent thing. I can keep practicing and get better, and maybe try out again next year. The feeling won't last forever if I actually work on it.
takeaway: I guess I should try to remember that even if I'm feeling bad now, it's not gonna last forever. And that even small changes can make a difference over time.

Like, your brain can actually change how you feel about stuff over time, so just hang in there. It might take a while, but things can get better, even if it doesn't seem like it now.

So, I guess my feelings about tests changed over time, because I found a way to deal with them.
